China Aerospace sees progress in spinoff . China Aerospace International Holdings Ltd said on Friday the Hong Kong stock exchange had approved in principle the company ' s application of a proposed spinoff of its telecommunications equipment maker . " The stock exchange has notified the company that the listing committee has approved in principle the application in relation to the proposed listing , " the electronics maker said in a statement . " The proposed listing is still subject to the final approval by the listing committee of the stock exchange . " China Aerospace said an announcement would be made when the final details of the proposed offering had been finalised and approved by the stock exchange . The company proposed to spin off its telecommunications equipment manufacturing and global positioning systems operations through a separate listing of a newly formed subsidiary . - - Hong Kong newsroom ( 852 ) 2843 6370 
